keep in mind that the author Pondsmith is from the school of the late 80s and early 90s, in which era RPG rules became very dense or “crunchy” whether or not they were of any service to the gameplay itself, and all of this generally following in the wake of the notion that this is the kind of technical detail that would seem convincing and inspirational to potential customers, most of whom were perforce GMs themselves and would not simply play the rules as purchased right out of the book but rather translated, as it were, through their own homebrewed systems
Red, though but lately published, is a purebred descendant of this worldview, which feels a bit rickety judge against more abstract and narrative-focused systems that have come into fashion since those days and afterward

>=400pg/mL is pretty high for cis f cycle lvls during late follicular, and similar for pregnancy lvls which can far exceed 1000pg/mL e2

if Kuhn, Lakatos, Feyerabend, Latour, Mirowski & others are right there’s no difference between contexts of discovery & justification—they are co-extensive in practice. Science is thus a set of virtues, as Merton, Popper, Shapin, Galison, Daston, Foucault & others argue. What’s more, social facts are often discursive & public in nature (Searle), epistemically and/or ontologically real (Searle, Haslanger, Epstein, Mirowski), taken for granted, epistemically performed (MacKenzie, Barad) & always involve truth & power (Foucault, Harraway, Jasanoff). Uniting this is the idea of pragmatics—pragmatics is the realm of context, force & intent—Austin/Grice/Searle’s implicature, Peirce’s index, Wittgenstein’s way of life, Bakhtin’s heteroglossia, Jakobson/Labov’s referentiality (& arguably Saussure’s parole, Chomsky’s performance). And, elaborating on that, meta-pragmatics, coined by Michael Silverstein, concerns the way language is used to specify correct use, to specify how to relate to context & intent, and instruct people on the proper social/extra discursive aspects of communication & discourse. At the end of the day, the definitions of words (semantics) & their baptism (meta semantics), the correct use of syntax, logical operators & rules, the correct way to take turns, use dialects, dispute & justify intent, reference & logic are all meta pragmatics—there’s no outside.

Why do you want this kind if family around you if they're obviously not going to be a healthy influence on you moving forward?
>I think this way I can explain my side thoroughly and do my best to get them to understand. Coming out will cause drama regardless, so I figure I might as well control my side of the narrative.
I used to think this way about my own family, but I eventually realized I was only doing it out of a sense that I had to "earn" my freedom from them in the form of some kind of logical debate on why I was doing what I was doing. This is not who you have to be though, because this is the position of a child asking their parents permission. You're an adult, you don't need permission or approval from your family now. If you want to tell them something, for any reason, you don't need to frame it like you're trying to win. You simply tell them what it is that you're doing, and then let them live with it on their own terms, because your parents are not your responsibility. They brought you into the world, not the other way around.

HAPPY NEW YEAR Edition
previous: >>28971086

Goal of the thread: Try to make concrete, sustainable resolutions. Keep your goals small and in reach so you don't get discouraged and actually get to work on them!

>What is this thread for?
Getting better is hard, and sucks. A lot. It does not get easier doing it alone.
Share resources and experiences with combating depression, anxiety, personal issues, achieving or maintaining a healthy weight, etc.
>Why is this thread /lgbt/?
Struggles with mental and physical health are an indisputable part of /lgbt/ life, be it from dysphoria, social pressure, heartbreak, or just unfortunate lifestyle choices.
>Notes to consider:
Please be civil. Shame is your greatest enemy in fighting urges of self abuse (be it sh, drugs, or just self deprecation). Relapsing into bad and unhealthy habits is to be expected, the goal is to increase the average amount of time it takes between relapses. Any improvement is a victory no matter how small. Your worth and right to get better are non-negotiable. And most importantly:
WE ARE NOT THERAPISTS, WE DON'T REPLACE MEDICATION
>Note on advice
Generic advice won't necessarily help you in particular, but for those it does it is an essential foundation to build future progress on, not a miracle cure. Do not underestimate the effects subtle changes to your lifestyle can have. Try first, keep us posted on your progress, build from there.
